âœ… Problem: Overlapping Intervals
Given an array of intervals arr[][], merge all overlapping intervals and return the result as a list.

ðŸ§  Example:
lua
Copy
Edit
Input:  [[1,3], [2,4], [6,8], [9,10]]
Output: [[1,4], [6,8], [9,10]]
âœ… Key Concepts:
ðŸ”¹ Overlapping Intervals:
Two intervals [a, b] and [c, d] overlap if:

r
Copy
Edit
b >= c
âœ… Steps to Solve:
Sort the intervals by their start time:
Arrays.sort(arr, (a, b) -> Integer.compare(a[0], b[0]));

Initialize an empty list:
List<int[]> merge = new ArrayList<>();

Iterate through sorted intervals:

If merge is empty OR current interval does not overlap â†’ add it.

Else, merge with last interval in list:

java
Copy
Edit
merge.get(merge.size() - 1)[1] = Math.max(lastEnd, currentEnd);
âœ… Java Code:
java
Copy
Edit
import java.util.*;

class Solution {
    public List<int[]> mergeOverlap(int[][] arr) {
        List<int[]> merge = new ArrayList<>();

        Arrays.sort(arr, (a, b) -> Integer.compare(a[0], b[0]));

        for (int[] interval : arr) {
            if (merge.isEmpty() || merge.get(merge.size() - 1)[1] < interval[0]) {
                merge.add(interval);
            } else {
                merge.get(merge.size() - 1)[1] = Math.max(
                    merge.get(merge.size() - 1)[1], interval[1]
                );
            }
        }

        return merge;
    }
}
âœ… Time & Space Complexity:
Aspect	Complexity
Time	O(n log n) â†’ due to sorting
Space	O(n) â†’ for result list

âš ï¸ O(n) time only possible if input is already sorted by start time.

